<div id="accordion">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h5 class="mb-0">
        <button class="btn btn-link" id="<%= tool_name%>-help-heading" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#<%= tool_name %>-help" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="<%= tool_name %>-help">
          pwnVNC Help
        </button>
      </h5>
    </div>

    <div id="<%= tool_name %>-help" class="collapse" data-toggle="collapse" aria-labelledby="<%= tool_name %>-help-heading" data-parent="#accordion">
      <div class="card-body bg-light">
        <pre style="margin-bottom:0;">pwnVNC checks if a host and service pair is a vnc server that allows unauthenticated logins, and if so, takes a screenshot of the vnc server

When a service is found: pwnVNC %ip% %port%
friendly name: check vnc
run in BG: true

Output files like vnc-somefile.txt will be automatically parsed into the UI. Output file names generated from this page are automatically appended with "vnc-" and prepended with ".txt"</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<div class="container no-gutters">
  <form id="<%= tool_name %>-options">
    <div class="row">
      <div class='col-sm-6'>    
        <%= erb :'tools/tool_helpers/_text_input', locals: {
                  tool_name: tool_name,
                  label: "Target",
                  field_name: "target",
                  field_value: "",
                  placeholder: "127.0.0.1"
                }
        %>

        <%= erb :'tools/tool_helpers/_text_input', locals: {
                  tool_name: tool_name,
                  label: "Port",
                  field_name: "port",
                  field_value: "5900",
                  placeholder: ""
                }
        %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
  <hr>
  <%= erb :'partials/_tool_runner', layout: false, locals: {tool_name: tool_name} %>
</div>
